African swine fever [ASF], Belgium
----------------------------------
Information received on [and dated] 14 Sep 2018 from Dr Jean-Fran√ßois Heymans, Director, Animal Health and Safety of Products of Animal Origin, Federal Agency for the Safety of the Food Chain (FASFC), Brussels, Belgium

Summary
Report type: immediate notification
Date of start of the event: 9 Sep 2018
Date of confirmation of the event: 12 Sep 2018
Reason for notification: Recurrence of a listed disease
Date of previous occurrence: 1985
Manifestation of disease: Clinical disease
Causal agent: African swine fever virus
Nature of diagnosis: laboratory (advanced), necropsy
This event pertains to the whole country

New outbreaks (2)
Outbreak 1: Etalle, [Walloon municipality], Luxembourg [province]
Date of start of the outbreak: 9 Sep 2018
Outbreak status: continuing (or date resolved not provided)
